<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">

	<p n="1">
		Prosperity! Fortune!
	</p>

	<p n="2-3">
		Eleventh year of the victorious king Kampavarman.
	</p>

	<p n="3-4">
		We the villagers of Kīḻppūtūr in the Kāliyūrkōṭṭam.
	</p>

	<p n="4-6">
		The manner in which <supplied reason="subaudible">we</supplied> gave ...
	</p>

	<p n="6-18">
		We have given, after sale, ...
	</p>

	<p n="18-23">
		In this manner, ...
	</p>

	<p n="23-25">
		...
	</p>

	<p n="25-27">
		...
	</p>

	<p n="27-28">
		We have given, after sale, ...
	</p>

	<p n="28-29">
		The then ruling king should protect <supplied reason="subaudible">this transaction</supplied>.
	</p>

	<p n="29-30">
		We, ..., the villagers of the above-mentioned Kīḻppūtūr.
	</p>

	<p n="30-32">
		While the villagers talked, I, Ṛṣikeśavabhaṭṭa, a member of the assembly <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kūṭṭam</foreign></supplied>, I wrote.
	</p>

	<p n="33-34">
		The feet of he who protects this pious act are on my head.
	</p>

</div>

